# TECHNICAL STANDARDS: THE 4 PILLARS (STRICT COMPLIANCE)
All code generation MUST adhere to these rules:

## 1. Strict Separation of Concerns (Service Layer)
- UI Components: MUST be "Thin". Only handle display, local state, and interactions.
- Business Logic: MUST reside in `services/`. NEVER fetch data directly inside UI or Hooks.
- Hooks: Use only as light wrappers to call the service layer.[cite: 8]

## 2. Resilience: The "2-Second Rule"
- All non-critical data fetching (Related products, Ads, etc.) MUST use `withTimeout` from `lib/timeout.ts` (2000ms limit).[cite: 8]
- Always provide a fallback (Skeleton or empty state) if data fails or times out.[cite: 8]

## 3. Performance & LCP Optimization
- Hero/Banner Images: MUST use `next/image` with `priority={true}`.[cite: 8]
- CLS Prevention: Every image container MUST have a defined aspect ratio or dimensions.[cite: 8]
- Use WebP compression as a default standard.[cite: 6]

## 4. Error & Loading Boundaries
- Every route MUST have `error.tsx` and `loading.tsx` to handle failures gracefully.[cite: 8]
- Provide clear, user-friendly error messages using Shadcn UI.[cite: 8]

# CORE CODING RULES
- **Language:** Code & Comments in English. Communication with "บอส" in Thai.[cite: 1]
- **Types:** STRICT TypeScript. Avoid `any` at all costs.[cite: 1]
- **Design:** Mobile-first, Boutique feel, using Teal (#12463e) and Lavender tokens.[cite: 1, 6]
- **Bilingual:** Standardize TH/EN support in all UI and SEO metadata.[cite: 1]
- **Case-Insensitivity:** Use `.toLowerCase()` for filtering logic consistently.[cite: 8]

# WORKFLOW & AUTOMATION
- After finishing a task, AUTOMATICALLY update `docs/blueprint/6_PROJECT_STATE.md`.[cite: 1, 8]
- Move tasks to COMPLETED, list exact files changed, and provide a logic summary.
- If a request contradicts the Blueprint, alert "บอส" immediately before proceeding.[cite: 1]

"Every time I ask for an update, scan the /app directory and compare it with the blueprints to ensure architecture consistency."